Sometimes it be like this 🤌
.
I’d be lying if I told you it was this easy all the time! 😅 Fished this Delayed Harvest stream for at least 3 hours with not a sign of interest from a trout.  This was my first time there since they stocked the first week of October & November.  I’m one who can easily get stuck in one non-productive spot forever with high hopes, but yesterday I covered a lot of water! Still nothing (and honestly I assume there have been poachers out). The water was also very low and clear as it’s been for a couple months.  As I was walking down the trail along the river on the way back to the truck, I picked out one last spot to try.  Got a trout on the first cast…and the 5 consecutive casts! All hitting in the same exact spot in the smallest hole!  2 Rainbows & 4 Brookies in less than 5 minutes!  I really couldn’t believe they kept biting with all the commotion going on with the other fish I was catching!  Nothing of much size, but it definitely filled my happy cup.  Everything is fun on the 3wt Glass Butterstick! After fish 6 and no bite the next cast I decided to leave on that seeing I was on my way home anyway! Fly fishing is fun sometimes 😜
.
.

I can’t believe it’s been 5 years to this day that I caught my first Louisiana Bull Red! 
.
I’ve fished for Redfish in MS, LA, all over FL, GA, SC & NC.  In my opinion…nothing compares to the fishery in LA.  I’ve spent a lot of time going out of Hopedale Marina & being WAY back in the marsh without a building or another boat around and so many amazing fish willing to eat! I haven’t had the same experience anywhere else I’ve fished yet! 

Hopefully I’ll finally be returning there in the New Year! This time I’m on a mission for my first BULL RED ON FLY!!!!! 🙌
.
If any fly fishing ladies would like to join me….DM me! 

AND I’m also looking for recommendations for a fly fishing guide out of either Hopedale Marina or possibly Bay St.Louis/Pass Christian, MS (my old home ☺️).
.

No trending music needed…..Everyone needs a “Hype-Mom” like mine!!! On this day, mom and I both fished for probably 3 hours with no bites…not even a sign of a fish.  On the way to the car we stopped at the run we originally started at.  First cast…I got this big girl! My mom netted it for me! 💪 Right after that…I let my mom use my euro rod & she immediately hooked up! Yes, she has noticed that I catch more on the euro, so now she wants one! We were each so happy we caught a fish we were ready to leave after 4 hours! 😅 It was a two & done day! I’m am so lucky to have a mom that wanted to learn to fly fish with me! She now even ties flies! She wont give me my vise back! haha. Some days fishing is easy and others can be extremely frustrating, but me & mom stick through it.  I love you @sleu38 & can’t wait for you to get a big one Monday! 🫶
.

* They call me “butter” 🧈because I’m “on a roll!” 🥐*

Everytime I catch on my glass Butterstick that’s what I think of! 😂 When I taught 6th grade math years ago (mid 20’s) that’s what we would call the kids when they answered a lot of questions right! 😅 I bet they thought I was such a nerd!! In my defense…my co-teacher started it not me! 
.
Jokes aside…I typically carry two rods….if I’m not euronymphing I’m usually using my “Butterstick” glass rod from @redingtongear (seen partially in this pic 😆). I’ve now caught trout, peacock bass, largemouth bass, small smallies lol & more on it! Even panfish are fun on the 4wt Butter! 🧈
.

Have I saved probably 100 different “audios” to make a year end review reel???…YES….will I make one?…maybe but probably not.

While it’s good/fun to reflect on your successes…and sometimes the losses…I’ve been working HARD this year to stay in “the present moment” as much as possible. 

Do I have things I would like to accomplish in 2023?!? OF COURSE and I’m stoked for things I have planned! But will I set a resolution? Absolutely not. Will I set goals….absolutely! Will I dwell on them?!? I don’t think so! That was not the case just a few years ago! Anxiety & fear of the future has had a HARD grip on me most of my life….until now! ☺️

One of my favorite quotes is:
“If you want to feel sad, live in the past…
If you want to feel anxious, live in the future…
If you want to feel peaceful, live in the now”

So that’s what I’m doing…I’m continuing to strive to live a peaceful life one minute at a time (and I also like to say one cast at a time). 

Instead of highlight reel of 2022….I’m going to post what is currently making me happy! Yesterday I caught my last fish of 2022…I’m also pretty certain it may be my new PB trout…not sure because I never measure them! 

You guys really seemed to enjoy this video when I posted it on my story…it had to have a spot on my page! My last post of 2022! I hope the excitement I get with every single fish never gets old!!!!! 

Happy New Years Eve my friends!!! Remember to take life one cast at a time this new year! 😘🥂🥳🍾🎉

PS- did y’all notice that bend in my Butterstick?!? Sexy!!! 🧈🧈🧈 @redingtongear 
.

What is a go to fly you have in your box?!? A fly that you may not use everytime you fish, but always have on hand….

If you are new to trout fishing on fly like me…..then you KNOW how overwhelming it can be to learn about flies when you are just trying your hardest to wade the river and make a roll cast without getting in the tree.

I hate to break it to you, but if you hope to go out on your own…without a guide & catch…you will at least need to know the basics about what fly to use in what conditions, what time of year, and at what kind of stream ( is it wild water or stocked water?). This has been an extremely long learning process for me…which is now why I’m sharing what I’ve learned as a newbie with you! 

I’ve been asked to start blogging this year & I will definitely be writing more in depth about this topic for you & sharing all I know.  Remember folks…I’m not an expert…just a fishing enthusiast who left the spin rod & the beach behind for the mountains 2 years ago. 

Back to the question I started off with! 👆I probably can name 4 flies that I will always have in my box trout fishing here in Western North Carolina.  In my years learning, I’ve come to find that a prince nymph typically gets the job done year round.  I usually don’t fish them under an indicator, but I always have one on my euronymphing rod.  I’m not going to lie….I’m not one to try a million different flies….when I find something that works, I tend to stick with it!  I’ve found that I mainly catch wild fish on it!  If I’m out targeting freshly stocked fish I would probably switch to one of my other go to’s I’ll tell you about in an upcoming post!  Hope this post was somewhat insightful for other beginners out there!

I think back to my first time going in the fly shop and having ZERO clue what in the world to choose….now ya know the name of one…thank me later! 😉
.

NEW PB Brook Trout TODAY!!!!! It was a Meat Eater!!!! Y’all I’m so excited about this beast of a brook trout! As most of you know- I’ve really dedicated the last couple weeks to bluelining for Native Appalachian Brookies!  But, I switched things up today! I hit one of my favorite DH rivers for stocking day (the first we’ve had since early fall)….hoping to land some big trout (bc we all know I need practice fighting bigger fish 😅). Well I broke a couple HUGE ones off that swam downstream into the rapids, but then this guy came along! Definitely my new PB Brook Trout (stocker). What a fun fight & day! PS- I met two fly fishing girls on the the river today, but sadly we didn’t trade into! Girls if you see this please DM me!  I love seeing other girls solo fly fishing!  Also, thank you for the “mini meat” @bcwmahony! 👊I definitely need a new order filled asap! Im addicted! They caught every cast!

“I prefer to earn it myself.  It makes me appreciate it more!”🤌

If you have any questions about getting into fly fishing or spin fishing without having to hire a guide, pay to fish private water or have a boat….please don’t hesitate to DM me! ☺️ Solo WADE fishing is one of the most rewarding things I’ve ever done not to mention the mindfulness and grounding it comes with! I began teaching myself saltwater/fresh spin fishing close to 20 years ago!  I began fly fishing about 5 years ago when my parents moved to Asheville, NC.  I moved to Asheville 2 years ago and it was then that a really got serious about learning to fly fish and I do it at least 3 times a week.  I don’t claim to be an expert at fly fishing, but I’m definitely getting the job done & sharing what I know with others brings me the greatest joy! 

If you are in the Surrounding Asheville area or plan on traveling here soon….they just stocked all of the Delayed Harvest Streams.  I caught this rainbow & more on the Shelton Laurel River a couple days ago in the Marshall/Hot Springs area! It’s a great place for beginners with lots of big fish! Many guides bring their clients there, so I would suggest going pretty early before they get there or around noon/1ish when most guide trips end and afternoon guide trips are about to start so you can secure a good fishing location! They will be stocking trout again the first week of April, May and I think June as well!  Help that info helps someone! 

~Ash

OK Mother Nature…we see you! 😍

Miles high into the blue ridge mountains lives a little gem only the faint at heart will seek to find.  The Southern Appalachian Brook Trout.  North Carolina’s only native trout! (They are actually in the Char family, but we will get to that another time)! These “trophy” fish grow only 6-8 inches, but their beauty & as well as the beautiful places they live brings me back over and over for more.

This moment right here. 

I have a million words to say about what went into this moment.  It’s something I’ve dreamed about since I was young & before I had ever touched a fly rod (every night no lie)! And now….on my 40th Birthday @citadelmarineservices & I made my dream reality.  I still can’t fully compose my thoughts because I’m still on ☁️9 and tear up everytime I look at this picture! I’ll for sure share more of the backstory behind this fish and how long I’ve been working for this soon! I’ve caught plenty of redfish on spin….they are the fish that made me fall in love with fishing in the beginning, but FINALLY on FLY! 
 
But know this…we didn’t see any redfish this evening for 3 hours UNTIL we spotted this guy tailing in the grass….literally the last few min of daylight. 

I’ve attempted this shot a few times over the years, but couldn’t ever get it done! That pressure that comes with sight fishing! 😅 I had one shot at this red and I actually MADE the cast!!!! Talk about some happy tears flowing!!!!!Capt. Rob didn’t cry in front of me, but I’m sure he was equally as happy! 😜

My first flood tide, tailing redfish…sight casted on FLY  perfectly in the grass! No other catch will ever give me the feeling of this one! It’s not about the size..it’s about conquering a dream.  I cannot wait to see what’s in store for me now that I kinda know what I’m doing Saltwater Fly Fishing! 

Thank you Capt. Rob for having me spend hours the day before practicing my double haul in 30 mph winds…and for the push 💨💨💨….this never would have happened if it weren’t for those lessons learned the day before in the worst conditions imaginable! 🤣

Happy 40th Birthday to me 🥳

It’s a special day today! 🎉 5 years ago today I caught my first trout! 

It was a Native Appalachian Brook Trout on a dry fly in the most beautiful location!  I was still living in South Florida at the time and was up in Asheville visiting my parents.  Little did I know I’d be living in the mountains now! I complain ALL the time about how much I miss living on the beach and saltwater fishing.  But I will admit….chasing these tiny native brookies in the most gorgeous, remote places is something not a lot of people get to do or are willing to do & I am grateful.  Being deep in the forest full of flowers, green moss, waterfalls, and some of the most gorgeous fish that God created is something I can’t get at the beach!

It’s like @natgeo up in here! 🐍🐟 Snake eats Wild Trout! 👀

Let me first say….I am NOT a snake fan! However, I’ve been wade fishing these WNC mountain streams for about 3 years now, so I’m slowly becoming more comfortable around them.

I refuse to watch anyone feed their pet snake, but I found watching this snake attack and feed off a Native Appalachian Brook Trout strangely intriguing. It’s the first time I’ve seen a snake feed in the wild before.  The Brookie was definitely alive when it was caught & not just a dead easy meal. 

Since I began fishing (and more so since fly fishing) I have a new appreciation for all things nature.  I feel so in tune with it.  I find myself spending as much time observing my surroundings as I do fishing! I’m not going to lie…seeing my favorite trout that’s so special to our state in the snakes mouth upset me for a couple seconds.  But then I couldnt stop watching!  I’ve seen birds prey on fish and swallow them in one gulp…but with the snake it was a long process! It was pretty cool watching the food chain out in the wild I must admit! I’m definitely on my way to becoming a full blown nature nerd! 

PS- the snake caught a bigger brookie than I did that day! Crazy to me because native brookies are so spooky!

A Labor of Love 💙

Spent my Labor Day Weekend the BEST way I know how! I may not teach Special Ed in the classroom anymore, but it is something I’m still extremely passionate about….in fact, I would have to say equally as fishing! So combine working with special needs & fishing….Ms.Underwood was in her happiest place! 

@castforkids has been around for over 30 years, but this was their first event ever in North Carolina!  Thank you SO much to @southernappalachiananglers for working with them to organize this event!

Also wanna give a big shout out to @jake_whitaker for taking all the kids out in his fancy bass boat! It was a HUGE hit!  For many people with special needs…sensory is a biggie! I was paired with Christian and his parents for the day! Christian was not one for tight spaces or being out on the pier.  His parents expressed to me that they thought having Christian out on the boat would help things! It worked! It was the only time the entire day that Christian held the fishing rod! It was a very special moment for all of us & so  proud of him! 🙌 Other parts of the day he LOVED being the net boy! Let’s all congratulate Christian for staying with us through the entire event and even coming up to accept his award plaque in front of everyone! Also, major props to his parents for getting him outdoors all while smiling, laughing and connecting with other parents with special needs kids. What a great weekend!

He seriously worked his ass off & was cheering me on till the last second! 👏 Keep in mind, I had only caught one redfish on fly prior to this! This tourney I learned the hard way about why not to “trout set” a redfish! 😆

While I didn’t get a red on the board this time, SO many ladies caught their first redfish on fly & that made my heart so happy! It was just this past May that I got that “first red on fly feeling” & it sure is special! 

Congrats @bredrake on your win!!! 

I see A LOT more saltwater fishing in my near future & excited to get back to my roots! See ya next year @mwladyred ❤️
